DocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zhm1665703132396.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zhm1665703132396.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zhm1665703132396.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zhm1665703132396\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__ufputc_402917\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Copy additional data from a program buffer into a Uniface field.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__topic_d119918e1_d119919e1_d119920e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104zhm1665703132396_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__codeblock_xhg_msz_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">short ufputc (unsigned char* field,unsigned char* buffer,short length);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__topic_d85362e1_d85363e1_d85364e1_d85365e1_d85366e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d682916e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__parml_iqx_nsz_zvb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">field</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The name of a field in your component. To resolve ambiguity, you can qualify the\n                  field name with an entity name, for example, <var class=\"keyword varname\">field</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">entity</var>. Instead of the actual field name, you also use the\n                  internal bind name as returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetbind</code>.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The data to be copied to the field. This data does not have to be\n                  zero-terminated.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">length</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The number of bytes that should be copied from <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var> to\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">field</var>. Use a negative value to indicate that more data is to\n                  follow (using additional calls to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code>).</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__topic_d85367e1_d85368e1_d85369e1_d85370e1_d85371e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d682916e121\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by ufput, ufputi, ufputc, and ufputext</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20__entry__1\"> Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20__entry__2\"> Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20__entry__1\">-1 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20__entry__2\">An error occurred.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20__entry__1\">0 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20__entry__2\">All data was copied to the field .</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20__entry__1\">1 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zhm1665703132396__d6834e20__entry__2\">There is more data to be copied to the field.\n                        Occurs when you have specified a negative <var class=\"keyword varname\">Length</var>\n                        value.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__topic_d85377e1_d85378e1_d85379e1_d85380e1_d85381e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d682916e185\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__topic_d85382e1_d85383e1_d85384e1_d85385e1_d85386e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d682916e198\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__p_d119957e1_d119958e1_d119959e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code> moves an additional block\n            of data from a program buffer to a Uniface field. Call this function only after a\n            previous call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufput</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputi</code> with a negative\n            length.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__p_d119960e1_d119961e1_d119962e1\">Parameters and return values are the same as for\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufput</code>. If you call <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code> with a negative length,\n            you must call it repeatedly until you use a non-negative <var class=\"keyword varname\">length</var>. For\n            more information, see the \"ufput\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__section_jcc_xsz_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d682916e227\">Example: ufput, ufputc, ufputi, and ugetbind</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example reads a graphics file from disk in chunks of 5000\n            bytes, and transfers the contents to the Uniface image field IMGFIELD. This field should\n            be defined in the form as:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__ul_kcc_xsz_zvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__li_d45158e1_d45159e1_d45160e1\">Data Type—Image (database)</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__li_d45161e1_d45162e1_d45163e1\">Widget Type—Picture </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__li_d45164e1_d45165e1_d45166e1\">Interface—R*</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">Note that, in the calls to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufput</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code>, we specify a negative length, because we are not sure if\n            there is more data until we have read the entire file. Once we have read all the file,\n            we issue a final call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufputc</code> with length zero to denote that the\n            transfer is complete.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104zhm1665703132396_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"zhm1665703132396__codeblock_xqm_zsz_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;\nEXPORT void GETIMAGE ()\n{\nFILE* fp;\nshort len;\nchar buf[5000];\nchar bindname[80];\n\n/* Use bindname for efficiency */\nugetbind(\"IMGFIELD\", bindname);\n/* Open binary read mode */\nfp = fopen(\"d:\\\\temp\\\\mypicture.jpg\", \"rb\");\nlen = fread(buf, 1, 5000, fp); /* Read first chunk */\nufput(bindname, buf, -len); /* Assume more to come */\nwhile (len &gt; 0)\n{\nlen = fread(buf, 1, 5000, fp); /* Read next chunk */\nif ( len &gt; 0 ) /* Assume more to come */\nufputc(bindname, buf, -len);\n}\nufputc(bindname, buf, 0); /* Tell Uniface it's done */\nfclose(fp); /* and close file */\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cyq1665703132133.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufput</a><p>Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534448\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534448\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ufputc Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Copy additional data from a program buffer into a Uniface field. Explain this code short ufputc (unsigned char* field,unsigned char* buffer,short length); Copy Parameters field The name of a field in your component. To resolve ambiguity, you can qualify the field name with an entity name, for example, field . entity . Instead of the actual field name, you also use the internal bind name as returned by ugetbind . buffer The data to be copied to the field. This data does not have to be zero-terminated. length The number of bytes that should be copied from buffer to field . Use a negative value to indicate that more data is to follow (using additional calls to ufputc ). Return Values Table 1. Values returned by ufput, ufputi, ufputc, and ufputext Value Meaning -1 An error occurred. 0 All data was copied to the field . 1 There is more data to be copied to the field. Occurs when you have specified a negative Length value. Use Library: yrtl Description ufputc moves an additional block of data from a program buffer to a Uniface field. Call this function only after a previous call to ufput or ufputi with a negative length. Parameters and return values are the same as for ufput . If you call ufputc with a negative length, you must call it repeatedly until you use a non-negative length . For more information, see the \"ufput\" topic. Example: ufput, ufputc, ufputi, and ugetbind The following example reads a graphics file from disk in chunks of 5000 bytes, and transfers the contents to the Uniface image field IMGFIELD. This field should be defined in the form as: Data Type—Image (database) Widget Type—Picture Interface—R* Note that, in the calls to ufput and ufputc , we specify a negative length, because we are not sure if there is more data until we have read the entire file. Once we have read all the file, we issue a final call to ufputc with length zero to denote that the transfer is complete. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #include <stdio.h> EXPORT void GETIMAGE () { FILE* fp; short len; char buf[5000]; char bindname[80]; /* Use bindname for efficiency */ ugetbind(\"IMGFIELD\", bindname); /* Open binary read mode */ fp = fopen(\"d:\\\\temp\\\\mypicture.jpg\", \"rb\"); len = fread(buf, 1, 5000, fp); /* Read first chunk */ ufput(bindname, buf, -len); /* Assume more to come */ while (len > 0) { len = fread(buf, 1, 5000, fp); /* Read next chunk */ if ( len > 0 ) /* Assume more to come */ ufputc(bindname, buf, -len); } ufputc(bindname, buf, 0); /* Tell Uniface it's done */ fclose(fp); /* and close file */ } Copy Related Links ufput Copy data from a program buffer into a Uniface field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}